         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">16/3/87. ¶  ¶ If I do not write much, dear Mr Dyer, you will know, it is not from want of attachment to Kew, but by the force of overwhelming work. The ¶  ¶ "Key" ¶  ¶ is still far from completion, an...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.03.16a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-90, ff. 220-1.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Stamped</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Royal Gardens Kew 2. May. 1887;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Annotated in ink by J. Baker</seg>:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Selaginella</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sent from Endeavour River [Coll.] Persieh is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">[pron]iflora</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Baker<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>JGB,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">and in pencil by W. Thiselton-Dye</seg>r And 4.5.87<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">[letter not found]</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>16/3/87.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If I do not write much, dear Mr Dyer, you will know, it is not from want of attachment to Kew, but by the force of overwhelming work. The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Key"<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is still far from completion, and daily duties of routine are always heavy anyhow. Yesterday I gave evidence on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"forests"<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>before a parliamentary Commission.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>16 March 1887, p. 9, col. 6; see Frost &amp;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>S.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Harvey (1997).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Forest-affairs look very gloomy for the next century anywhere in readily accessible regions.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I greet with delight your Bulletin!<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The first part of Kew's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Bulletin of miscellaneous information</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was published in January 1887.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Some thing of the kind I had in contemplation, if I could have remained in the Garden.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Prof Luerssen has only examined yet a small portion of the Papuan Ferns, so I have resolved, to send to Kew fragments of each species;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For the circumstances leading to M sending ferns to Luerssen see M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 22 June 1886.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from what little I have, only small pieces can be spared, as Sydney and Brisbane have also to be supplied. But to keep faith with Dr Luerssen I would beg of Mr Baker to communicate with him on any species which may perhaps prove new; — Mr Forbes ferns did not come here.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M refers to the New Guinea collections of Henry Forbes; the ferns went to the British Museum (Natural History).</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Red pencil line in margin against</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I would beg … proves new.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">The initials<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>JGB [John Gilbert Baker]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">are alongside the line</seg>.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See notes to M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 17 February 1886<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 86-02-17a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Mr Davidson, who went with Mr Sayer on a mission of mine to the summit of Mt Bellenden Ker,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Qld.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will, (if he does not alter his plans) return next month to England, where his father is the Proprietor of a Great Iron factory. The young Gentleman will bring you the small case with rooted plants of the redflowering Correa Lawrenciana. Though<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Red pencil line in margin against</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will bring … though<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Annotated in lead pencil in margin<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>Not yet rec 10-8-87 W.W. [William Watson]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">and</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Failed, see lett 4/7/87<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">[i.e. M to W</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">. Thiselton-Dyer, 4 July 1887</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">(in this edition as 87-07-04a)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">which arrived at Kew on 22 August 1887].</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>hardier than any other species, it should arrive in Spring at Kew. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>It<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was Mr Findlay,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Findlay.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>after whom I named the Bertya Findlay[aea],<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>after whom … Findlay[aea]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">is a marginal note with intended position indicated by an asterisk. The end of the word is cramped at edge of sheet, but it is definitely not the correct Findlayi</seg>.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>who kindly got the cuttings for the second time and planted them in pots. So they came here, where they have been under my care for many month on the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">few square yards</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of garden-ground at my little Cottage.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope, that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">these</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>particular cuttings will also show the brilliant color of the var cardinalis of C. speciosa, such as I saw when 1873<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn9" n="10">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>1873<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">interlined</seg>.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I discovered in one single valley the red flowered C. Lawrenciana. Speaking of the bid<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn10" n="11">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>bit?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of ground on which I dwell, I am reminded of Seume's words<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">"Von allen diesen fetten Gaunen</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Gehöret mir ja nicht,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">ein Fussbreit Land um Kohl darauf zu bauen,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Zu einem ländlichen Gericht."<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn11" n="12">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M is evidently quoting from memory, and somewhat misquoting, from<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'Abschiedschreiben an Münchhausen'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1792) by Johann Gottfried Seume (1763-1810):</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.9298in; text-indent: -0.3298in; "
                        xml:lang="en">Ich habe von den vielen fetten Gauen,</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.9298in; text-indent: -0.3298in; "
                        xml:lang="en">Auch keinen Fuss, mir meinen Kohl zu bauen</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.9298in; text-indent: -0.3298in; "
                        xml:lang="en">Zu einem ländlichen Gericht.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Which, if I may fuse<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn12" n="13">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M is using a figurative sense of an archaic meaning of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'fuse', namely<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'to set out hastily'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(OED).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>it in English language, might be [put]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn13" n="14">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Word obscured by binding.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">"Of all the rich and verdant tillage,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Not so much is my share,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">To grow a single dish of cabbage,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">For a plain rural fare!"</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Mr Davidson will give you if you like a verbal account of the dangers and toil to ascend Mt Bellenden Ker.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Just had a glorious letter from Asa Gray<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn14" n="15">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Bertya Findlayaea</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Correa Lawrenciana</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Correa speciosa var cardinalis</p>
         </div>
